{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"**Topology Summary**\nUse a classic resistive-load NMOS inverter. A pull-up resistor `R` connects `VDD` to `Vout`, and a single NMOS transistor pulls `Vout` down to ground when `Vin` exceeds threshold. This is explicitly not CMOS, so no PMOS device is used.\n\n**Device/Function List**\n- `VDD`: independent DC supply from `VDD` to `0`, value `5 V`.\n- `Vin`: independent input voltage source from `Vin` to `0`, swept in DC analysis.\n- `R`: pull-up/load resistor from `VDD` to `Vout`, nominally `10k`.\n- `M1`: NMOS pull-down transistor.\n  - Drain: `Vout`\n  - Gate: `Vin`\n  - Source: `0`\n  - Bulk: `0`\n- NMOS model: threshold set to `0.7 V`, e.g. `VTO=0.7`.\n\n**Bias/Reference Strategy**\nGround node is `0`. `VDD` is fixed at `5 V`. `Vin` must be driven by an explicit voltage source so the gate is never floating. The NMOS source and bulk are tied to ground to avoid body-bias ambiguity.\n\n**Signal or Feedback Path**\nThere is no feedback path. The signal path is feed-forward: `Vin` controls the NMOS gate, which modulates pull-down current from `Vout` to ground. `R` continuously pulls `Vout` toward `VDD`.\n\nExpected DC behavior:\n- `Vin < Vth`: NMOS off, `Vout` near `5 V`.\n- `Vin > Vth`: NMOS conducts, `Vout` is pulled low through the NMOS.\n- Transition is gradual due to resistive load and transistor conduction strength.\n\n**SPICE/Netlist Constraints**\n- Final filename must be `p6.cir`.\n- Preserve exact port names: `Vin`, `Vout`.\n- Include:\n  - `VDD VDD 0 DC 5`\n  - `Vin Vin 0 DC ...`\n  - resistor from `VDD` to `Vout`\n  - NMOS `M1 Vout Vin 0 0 <model>`\n  - NMOS model with `VTO=0.7` or equivalent\n  - `.dc Vin 0 5 0.1`\n- Nominal sizing such as `W=10u L=1u` is acceptable.\n\n**Failure Risks To Avoid**\n- Do not add a PMOS transistor.\n- Do not omit the independent `Vin` source; `.dc Vin ...` requires a source named `Vin`.\n- Do not rename `Vin` or `Vout`.\n- Do not leave the NMOS bulk floating.\n- Do not connect the resistor to ground; it must pull up from `VDD` to `Vout`.\n- Do not reverse the intended NMOS role: drain should be `Vout`, source and bulk should be `0`."}}
